Source: aptura-kernel
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Aptura <packages@aptura.example>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: aptura-kernel
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 linux-image-@KERNEL_VERSION@-aptura,
 linux-headers-@KERNEL_VERSION@-aptura
Description: Aptura OS custom kernel selector
 Pulls in the Aptura-branded custom mainline kernel (@KERNEL_VERSION@-aptura)
 built from kernel/ and served by the local Aptura repository. Keeping this as
 a metapackage means the default kernel version is changed in one place
 (config/distro.env) and rebuilt.
